  "prompt": "How do I start a diary entry?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to start a diary entry:\n\n1. Date and time\n- Write the date and time at the top of the page\n- Example: \"June 15, 2023 - 8:30 PM\"\n\n2. Mood or emotional state\n- Begin by describing how you're feeling\n- Example: \"Today I'm feeling overwhelmed but hopeful...\"\n\n3. A specific event or highlight\n- Start with something significant that happened\n- Example: \"Today was amazing because...\"\n\n4. A question or reflection\n- Open with a thought-provoking question or reflection\n- Example: \"I've been wondering lately...\"\n\n5. A quote or inspiration\n- Begin with a quote that resonates with you\n- Example: \"As Eleanor Roosevelt said...\"\n\n6. Simple greeting\n- Write a casual greeting to yourself\n- Example: \"Dear Diary,\" or \"Hey there!\"\n\n7. Stream of consciousness\n- Just start writing whatever comes to mind\n- Example: \"So much has happened today...\"\n\nTips:\n- Be honest and authentic\n- Don't worry about perfect writing\n- Write for yourself, not an audience\n- Choose a method that feels comfortable to you\n\nRemember, there's no \"right\" way to start a diary entry - just write!",
